**Amrit Brikshya Andolan & Ek Ped Maa Ke Naam campaign**

The *Amrit Brikshya Andolan* was launched by the Honourable Chief Minister of Assam on 8th June 2023\. The initiative has achieved a plantation of over 1.19 crore commercial saplings across the state with above 90% survival. In continuation to last year's achievement, the Honourable Chief Minister of Assam has announced in the Budget 2023-24 to plant 3 crore seedlings during 2024\.

In addition to Amrit Brikshya Andolan, the Government of Assam will be planting seedlings in the honour of mothers. The Honourable Prime Minister, Shri Narendra Modi has launched 'Ek Ped Maa Ke Naam' Campaign on the occasion of World Environment Day, 2024 and encouraged citizens “to plant a tree in the coming days as a tribute to your mother”. In Assam too, the Honourable Chief Minister requests everyone to plant a tree in the name of their mothers.

1. **Vision:** The *Amrit Brikshya Andolan* is a Jan Andolan to involve citizens in commercial tree plantation.

2. **Objective:** Its primary objective is to increase Tree Outside Forest (ToF) areas, to give a significant boost to the state’s green economy and the Agroforestry Sector by promoting commercial tree plantation, fostering sustainable practices, and enhancing Assam’s green cover.

#### **Standard Operating Procedure (SOP)**

3. **Focus:** To outline the procedure for seamless and effective distribution of saplings to the registered users under the *Amrit Brikshya Andolan* and the subsequent upload of photos on the day of plantation.

4. **Scope:** This SOP applies to all stakeholders (Self Help Group, ASHA (Health), Educational Institutions, Village Defense Party, Anganwadi workers, Tea Garden, Armed Forces, Farmer Organisations (FPC/ FPO), Social Organisations, Institutions, and other Individuals) involved in the plantation of saplings under the Amrit Brikshya Andolan.

5. **Responsibilities:** Field-level staff and line departments under which they are operating shall be jointly responsible for the distribution of the saplings and the successful execution of the drive.

## ***Forest Department***

1. #### **Forest Nursery/ Stocking Points**

   The Forest Nursery (FN) is the main stocking point from which the seedlings are distributed. However, Forest Nurseries, which may be inaccessible due to heavy rains, poor approach roads, and long distances from the distribution points, need to stock the seedlings at an alternate place/ site called Stocking Points (SP).

   1. ##### **Responsibilities**

      * The Forest Nursery/ Stocking Point Coordinator is responsible for the end-to-end audit of seedlings, covering both inward (in the case of SP) and outward movement.

   2. ##### **Facilities at Stocking Point**

      * Provide IN/OUT and turning space for trucks.

      * Ensure adequate space for seedling loading/unloading.

      * Maintain raised seedling beds (1000 each).

      * Erect cattle-proof perimeter fencing for security.

      * Assign staff for seedling care, watering, and shifting as required.

      * Establish shade and watering facilities.

   3. ##### **Staffing**

   *Each Forest Nursery/ Seedling Stocking Point should have:*

      * One designated Coordinator from the forest department.

      * One 2nd-in-Command (2 I/C) in the rank of Forester-I and above.

      * Their mobile numbers should be published for communication.

   4. ##### **Record Keeping**

      * Keep a stock register (as per FORMAT –I) for species-wise and bed-wise inventory for Forest Nurseries.

      * Maintain IN Registers (as per FORMAT \-III for SP) and OUT Registers (as per FORMAT – II for FN& FORMAT – IV for SP) to record all incoming and outgoing seedlings.

   5. ##### **Receipt Protocol at Stocking Point**

      * Receive seedlings with a Seedling Movement Challan (as per FORMAT \-VIII) for each consignment from Forest Nursery.

      * SPs shall enter the details of receipt of the seedlings from Forest Nursery in the Stocking Point IN register (as per FORMAT \-III).

6. ##### **Responsibility for Damage**

   * Damage of seedlings at the Stocking Point beyond 1% shall be the personal liability of the SP Coordinator.

     * Departmental action shall be taken in such cases.

   7. ##### **Distribution/shifting**

      * Use a SEEDLING MOVEMENT CHALLAN (as per FORMAT – VIII) for all outward movement of seedlings from the FN/ SP.

2. #### **Seedling Distribution Points (DP)**

   1. ##### **Responsibilities**

      * The distribution points include the Forest Nursery/ Stocking Points/ Distribution Points from where the beneficiaries can lift the seedlings depending upon the vicinity and their convenience.

      * The Distribution Point Coordinator is responsible for the end-to-end audit of seedlings, covering both inward and outward movement.

      * The Distribution Point Coordinator shall maintain a comprehensive record of distributed seedlings to Departments/ Institutions (as per FORMAT \-VI) & Individuals (as per FORMAT \-VII). Records shall include Registration IDs or Mobile Numbers.

   2. ##### **Facilities**

      * Provide IN/OUT space for the movement of vehicles.

      * Ensure sufficient space for seedling loading/unloading.

      * Install cattle-proof perimeter fencing for security.

      * Engage watch and ward personnel for seedling care.

      * Provide Daily Labour for the upkeep of Distribution Points and handling of the seedlings.

      * Establish shade facilities.

   3. ##### **Staffing**

*Each Seedling Distribution Point should have:*

* One designated Coordinator and one 2 I/ C appointed by the District Commissioner.

  * Appoint a record keeper to maintain seedling distribution records.

    * Their mobile numbers must be published.

    * No Forest Department staff shall be engaged.

  4. ##### **Record Keeping**

     * Maintain IN & OUT Registers (as per FORMAT \-V, VI & VII) to keep a record of all incoming and outgoing seedlings.

  5. ##### **Transportation**

     * Transportation from a Forest Nursery/ Stocking Point to a Distribution Point shall be the responsibility of the District Level Coordination Committee (DLCC).

     * The Transportation cost shall be defrayed by the Forest Department for specified distribution points.

  6. ##### **Receipt Protocol**

     * Reject damaged seedlings from the FN/ SP.

     * Receive seedlings with a SEEDLING MOVEMENT CHALLAN (as per FORMAT – VIII) for each consignment.

  7. ##### **Responsibility for Damage:**

     * Damage of seedlings at the Distribution Point beyond 1% shall be the personal liability of the Distribution Point Coordinator.

     * Departmental action shall be taken in such cases.

  8. ##### **Seedling Movement:**

     * Maintain a Distribution Point Out Register separately for organisations/ Institutions (as per FORMAT – VI) and for individual beneficiaries (as per FORMAT – VII) for all outward movement of seedlings from the Distribution Points.

3. #### **Seedling Transportation**

   1. ##### **Forest Department Responsibilities:**

      * Ensure each seedling movement has a valid SEEDLING MOVEMENT CHALLAN (as per FORMAT – VIII).

      * Provide adequate skilled labour for seedling handling during transportation.

      * All vehicles carrying the Amrit Brikshya Andolan seedlings shall prominently display the “**Amrit Brikshya Andolan**” & “**Ek Ped Maa Ke Naam**” banners at the front and back.

   2. ##### **Transportation from FN/SP to DP**

      * Each vehicle must have a valid SEEDLING MOVEMENT CHALLAN (as per FORMAT – VIII).

      * Each vehicle shall be accompanied by a Government Employee/ Staff designated by the District Level Coordination Committee.

3. ##### **Route Planning:**

   * The DLCC shall develop a transportation route plan for moving seedlings from FN/ SPs to various DPs in a way that minimises transportation expenses, time, and the number of trips required.

4. #### **Seedling Distribution**

   1. ##### **Distribution Schedules**

      * Distribution Dates: **1stto 12th August 2024\.**

      * Seedling dispatch from Forest Nursery to Stocking Points: Starts on **15th July and shall be over by 29thJuly 2024\.**

      * Seedling dispatch from Stocking Points to Distribution Points: Starts on **30th July** and shall be over by

      ##### **12th August 2024\.**

      * Beneficiaries shall collect seedlings from the Distribution Point between **1st to 12th August 2024**.

   2. ##### **Record-Keeping Protocol**

      * Seedlings shall be distributed only to the registered beneficiaries/ institutions/ individuals.

   3. ##### **Seedling preference**

      * Priority for premium species (*Agaru, Boga Chandan, Bogi Poma, Ghora Neem, Kadam, Mahogany,* and *Tita Sopa*) shall be given to Self-Help Groups, Farmers (FPO/ FPC), ASHA Workers, Anganwadi Workers & Village Defence Parties.

      * Priority for fruit-bearing species shall be given to Educational Institutions and social organisations.

   4. ##### **Shortage/Surplus of seedlings**

      * In the event of seedling shortages at any Distribution Point, the District Level Coordination Committee may source additional seedlings from surplus stock at the nearest Forest Nursery/ Stocking Point.

      * Any surplus seedlings that remain undistributed must be utilised as directed by the DLCC.

# Handling, Planting and Protection of Seedlings

5. #### **Key steps for handling, planting and Protection of Seedlings**

   ##### **The beneficiaries are required to observe the following:**

   1. **Handling of Seedlings**

* Handle seedlings with care to avoid damaging polythene or Pot Mixer.

* Water seedlings by sprinkling once daily.

* No watering two days before transportation.

* Beneficiaries shall water seedlings lightly once a day and keep them in the shade.

* No watering one day before planting.

  2. ##### **Handling of Seedlings**

* Watch “How to Plant” videos on the Mobile App, if in doubt.

* Dig a 1 foot x1 foot x1 foot pit at least 1 day before planting, mix pit soil with organic manure.

* Remove soil from the pit one day before planting.

* Carefully slit polythene without disturbing the soil.

* Fill the pit with soil mix, leaving the root collar at ground level.

* Remove polythene, place seedling, and fill the pit to prevent water-logging.

* Gently compact soil around the stem.

* Provide support with a taller bamboo stick, and tie with jute string.

* Water seedlings gently.

* Take a selfie with the seedling using the *Amrit Brikshya Andolan* Mobile App. The selfie will be geo-tagged, time-stamped, and framed by the App.

* Photographs of the planted seedlings also need to be uploaded on MeriLiFE Portal

  *(https://merilife.nic.in)*

* Upload separate selfies for each planted seedling.

* The planting is scheduled to start from **6.00 am on 1st August and continue till 6.00 pm on 15th August 2024\.**

  3. ##### **Protection of Seedlings**

* Create a DIY (Do it yourself) tree guard at home with three/four (Triangle/square) sticks around the seedling, leaving space for growth.

* Wrap the sticks around the sides with agro-net fabric/jute bags.

* Regularly care for and protect seedlings from grazing and fire until they grow into trees.

## ***Panchayat & Rural Development Department***

1. Distribution of Saplings under the Panchayat and Rural Development Department shall be done by the Assam State Rural Livelihoods Mission

   1. ##### **Primary Beneficiaries**

      * Under the Panchayat and Rural Development Department, Self-Help Groups are the primary beneficiaries of the Amrit Brikshya Andolan.

   2. ##### **Delivery of Seedlings**

      * The seedlings will be delivered by the Forest departments at the Gram Panchayat Offices and for the VIth Schedule areas at the Block Offices starting from **31st July to 12th August 2024,** from where SHGs are to collect the seedlings.

      * The SHGs shall collect the saplings from the Gram Panchayat Offices/Block level Offices (As mentioned above) between **1st August and 12th August 2024\.**

   3. ##### **Record Keeping**

      * The Department shall maintain a record of distribution of seedlings (as per FORMAT – VII).

        * The Nodal officers shall assist in planting and uploading a selfie with the planted seedlings on the Amrit Brikshya Andolan Mobile Application.

   4. ##### **Formation of Committees for the proper management and stockings of the seedlings**

      * A committee shall be formed at the Gram Panchayat level in the Panchayati Raj Institution (PRI) Districts and Block Level at the VIth Schedule Districts.

  5. ##### **Contact Information**

## ***Women and Child Development Department***

1. Under the Women and Child Development Department, Anganwadi Workers and Anganwadi Helpers are the primary beneficiaries of the *Amrit Brikshya Andolan*.

   1. ##### **Distribution of Saplings**

      * In respect of rural areas, the saplings shall be provided Gaon Panchayat (GP) wise.

      * In respect of urban areas, the saplings shall be provided Integrated Child Development Services (ICDS) Project wise.

      * The Department shall prepare the distribution plan submitted to the District Nodal officer by 18th July 2024\.

      * The seedlings will be delivered by the Forest departments at the GP Offices and for the VIth Schedule areas at the Block Offices starting from **31st July to 12th August 2024**, from where Anganwadi workers and Anganwadi helpers are to collect the seedlings.

      * The Anganwadi workers and Anganwadi helpers are to collect the saplings (As mentioned above) from the designated distribution points (GP offices/block level offices) between **1st August and 12th August 2024\.**

   2. ##### **Record Keeping**

      * The Department shall maintain a record of distribution of seedlings (as per FORMAT – VII).

      * Nodal officers shall assist in planting and uploading a selfie with the planted seedlings on the Amrit Brikshya Andolan Mobile Application.

   3. **Field-level implementation matrix:**

## ***Police Department***

1. Distribution of Saplings under the Police Department.

   ##### **Police Personnel and Homeguards**

   1. **Primary Beneficiaries**

      * Under the Police Department, Police Personnel, home guards and Village Defense Parties (VDPs) are the primary beneficiaries of the Amrit Brikshya Andolan.

      * Nodal officers shall assist in planting and uploading a selfie with the planted seedlings on the Amrit Brikshya Andolan Mobile Application.

   2. ##### **Delivery of Seedlings**

      * Seedlings for the police department shall be supplied by the Forest Department to the respective Police Stations/ Thana/ Battalion Headquarters starting from **31st July to 12th August 2024**.

      * The VDPs and police reserves shall collect the seedlings from the Police Stations starting from

      ##### **1stAugust to 12th August 2024**.

   3. **Record Keeping**

      * The Department shall maintain a record of distribution of seedlings (as per FORMAT – VII).

   4. ##### **Data Collection**

      * Collect information for Police Personnel and Home guards in an Excel sheet.

      * Circulate the information to all Senior Superintendents of Police, Commandants, and Range Senior Officers.

      * Gather data on a Police station-wise basis.

      * Consolidate the collected information.

      * Provide the consolidated data to the concerned Nodal department for record-keeping.

   5. ##### **Delivery of Seedlings**

      * Deliver plant saplings to Police Stations for Police Personnel, including Battalion personnel, and Home guards deployed in Police stations.

      * Deliver to the Police Reserve for Police Personnel in the SP office and Police Reserve.

      * Deliver to Battalion HQ for Police personnel deployed in Battalion HQ.

   ##### **Village Defense Party (VDP)**

   6. VDPs shall register individually on the Amrit Brikshya Andolan Portal.

   7. Delivery saplings for VDPs shall be done at the concerned Police Station.

   8. Distribution to VDPs will be managed from the Police Station.

Individuals and Institutions pre-registered in the App shall collect the seedlings between **1stAugust to 12th August 2024** from the designated distribution centres.

      * The Armed Forces shall plant seedlings and maintain a record of the planted seedlings.
